      "writtenOn": "2017-11-30T12:55:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It seemed like something that might be generally useful, and also in case we do decide to extend this behavior elsewhere.  We\u0027re at 14.6% mem usage on the VM right now.  I don\u0027t have a good breakdown of the major contributors, but I\u0027d assume that\u0027s a reasonable baseline for just the caches, since it\u0027s early and we don\u0027t have many task candidates in flight.  This CL would roughly quadruple the job cache memory usage (~2x adding the new map and 2x for a second instance).  We have ~500 jobs and ~800 tasks.  I\u0027d bet that we\u0027re still under 20% with this CL, but I can watch that (and other performance statistics) to verify.",
